Understanding Background Images & Images
	1) background properties:
		image, color, position, size, origin, clip, repeat, attachment.
	2) background Shorthand
		Escribir propiedades del background en una sola línea.
	3) filter property (hipster)
		blur, grayscale, contrast
	4) Gradients (fosforiloco)
		lineal and radial
	5) Multiple backgrounds
		only one solid color, using transparency can create cool effects
	6) <img> vs background-image
		img is better for accessibility but way more difficult to style.

Sizes & Units
	1) units
		px, %, rem & em, vh & vw, auto
	2) the containing block
		El % value varía dependiendo el { property: value } aplicado.
	3) { height:100% } issue
		Aveces esto no funciona, puedes resolverlo de varias formas.
	4) min/max-width
		Crear limitaciones a los elementos, sirve mucho para la responsividad.
	5) em & rem
		Tamaños que siempre dependen del font-size.

Making our Website Responsive
	1) Viewport <metatag>
		Convert hardware pixels to software pixels
	2) media queries
		@media

Working with Text and Fonts
	1) Generic families as fallback (browser families) in case font family is not available.
	2) Importing font families
		<link href...>	|	@import url(...)	|	@font-face{...}
	3) Some font properties
		size, style, weight, variant, letter-spacing, white-space, line-height...
	4) font-display
	5) font shorthand
		font: italic small-caps 700 1.2rem/2 "AnonymousPro", sans-serif;

Flexbox
	1) Flex-container, Flex items
	2) display: flex, display: inline-flex
	3) flex-direction, flex-wrap, align-items, justify-content, align-content
	4) Main axis vs Cross axis
	5) Flex items: order, align-self, flex-grow, flex-shrink, flex-basis.

